main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were observed over Corry, Pennsylvania on April 5, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were circular in shape and appeared to have a luminous corona around the outer edge.
The objects were observed to make abrupt changes in direction and perform other erratic maneuvers.
One object was observed first to the east, then moved to the northwest and disappeared.
Three objects were observed moving together in a northwesterly direction, with one executing a sharp right angle turn.
Two objects were observed moving toward the northeast at a high rate of speed.
